Morgan Lewis Hires Shearman Partner for Restructuring Practice

-- B y   C u l l e n   W h e a t l e y
-- 
2011-10-19T22:29:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-19/morgan-lewis-hires-shearman-partner-for-restructuring-practice.html
Morgan Lewis & Bockius LLP, the
largest Philadelphia-based  law firm  according to  Internet Legal
Research Group , said it hired a Shearman & Sterling LLP equity
partner to lead its New York restructuring practice.  Jim Garrity has provided counsel to Bank of America Corp,
Daimler AG, and Citigroup Inc, and he represented Eddie Bauer
Inc. in the company’s Chapter 11 case, Morgan Lewis said today
in a statement. He also has represented debtors, creditors and
court-appointed fiduciaries in Chapter 11 bankruptcy and cross-
border cases, according to the statement.  “Jim, who is among the most experienced bankruptcy lawyers
in New York, will help us continue to offer our clients robust
restructuring capabilities,” Charlie Engros, leader of the
firm’s business and finance practice, said in the statement.  Garrity was a bankruptcy judge in the Southern District of
 New York  before working at Shearman & Sterling LLP.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cullen Wheatley in New York at 
